http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kolkata/Taxi-hijack-1-held/article13994893.ece

One person was arrested from central part of city in connection with a taxi-hijacking incident late on Sunday night. Tanmoy Banerjee (19) a drug addict was arrested from his Amherst Street area on Monday afternoon on charge of hijacking the taxi from its driver Naresh Yadav at around 1.40 AM, police said.“Banerjee along with a friend hired the cab from Khelat Babu Lane in Tala Police Station limits and went to New Alipore. There from they went to Khilat Babu Lane and it was there where they beat up the driver and drove away with the vehicle along with Rs 16,000,” a police officer said.- PTI